people.aboutText: Lenka Němečková (born 20 April 1976 in Brno) is a former professional Czech tennis player.

people.name: Jon Hugger
people.aboutText: Jonathan "Jon" Hugger (born April 20, 1977) is an American professional wrestler. He is best known for his appearances with World Championship Wrestling as Johnny the Bull and World Wrestling Entertainment as Johnny Stamboli.

people.name: Meelis Rooba
people.aboutText: Meelis Rooba (born 20 April 1977) is an Estonian professional football coach and former player. Currently he is the head coach of Meistriliiga side Paide Linnameeskond.

people.name: Clayne Crawford
people.aboutText: Clayne Crawford (born April 20, 1978) is an American actor.

people.name: Rebecca Makkai
people.aboutText: Rebecca Makkai (born April 20, 1978) is an American novelist and short-story writer. Her first novel, The Borrower, was released in June 2011. It was a Booklist Top Ten Debut, an Indie Next pick, an O Magazine selection, and one of Chicago Magazine's choices for best fiction of 2011.

people.name: Mirei Kuroda
people.aboutText:
Mirei Kuroda (黒田 美礼, Kuroda Mirei, born 20 April 1978, in Saitama, Japan) is a famous Japanese swimsuit model. She was Fuji Television's "Visual Queen of the Year" in 1996.
^ Infobox data from: "黒田 美礼 (Kuroda Mirei)" (in Japanese).

people.name: Ludovic Magnin
people.aboutText:
Ludovic Magnin (born 20 April 1979 in Lausanne) is a former Swiss football defender.
^ "Ludovic Magnin" (in German). fcz.ch.

people.name: Nate Marquardt
people.aboutText: Nathan Joel Marquardt (born April 20, 1979) is an American mixed martial artist competing in the Middleweight division of the Ultimate Fighting Championship.

people.name: Tatyana Polnova
people.aboutText: Tatyana Polnova (Russian: Татья́на Полнова), née Zaykova (За́йкова, born 20 April 1979) is a Russian pole vaulter. Between 1998 and 2002 she competed for Turkey under the Turkish name Tuna Köstem. She is currently Fenerbahçe Athletics Club member.

people.name: Gregor Tait
people.aboutText: Gregor Tait (born 20 April 1979 in Glasgow) is a Scottish backstroke swimmer, and an Olympic swimmer for Great Britain.

people.name: Quinn Weng
people.aboutText: Quinn Weng (Chinese: 翁碩瑜, born April 20, 1979) is a Taiwanese-Canadian mezzo-soprano singer and is the lead vocalist of the power metal band Seraphim.

people.name: Gunta Baško
people.aboutText: Christopher Ellis Duffy (born April 20, 1980) is a former Major League Baseball outfielder.

people.name: Chris Duffy
people.aboutText:
Gunta Baško-Melnbārde (born Gunta Baško April 27, 1980, Riga, Latvia) is a Latvian women's basketball player currently playing for Basket Landes and Latvia women's national basketball team. She was born in Riga.
Baško first played in a professional team in 1995.

people.name: Arin Paul
people.aboutText: Jasmin Wagner ([jasˈmiːn ˈʋaːɡnɐ], born 20 April 1980), better known as Blümchen [ˈblyːmçən], is a pop and dance music singer, actress, and model/spokesperson. Although she releases her English albums under the name Blossom, her German stage name "Blümchen" actually translates to "floret" or "small flower". She is also known as Denim Girl, performing the song "Are You Ready For Some Darkness?" on the Alpha Motherfuckers - A Tribute to Turbonegro album.

people.name: Jasmin Wagner
people.aboutText: Arin Paul (born 20 April 1980) is a film director and writer.

people.name: Sefyu
people.aboutText: Youssef Soukouna (born 20 April 1981 in Goutte d'Or, Paris), better known by his stage name Sefyu (French pronunciation: ​[sɛˈfju], his first name in verlan), is a French rapper of Senegalese descent. He comes from Aulnay-sous-Bois (“Cité des Emmaüs”), a city in the French department of Seine-Saint-Denis (Northern suburbs of Paris). Sefyu originally aspired to become a professional soccer player, but his dream was derailed after he sustained an injury.

people.name: Saša Tabaković
people.aboutText: Saša Tabaković (born April 20, 1981) is a Slovenian actor, born to Bosnian parents. After finishing his studies at High School for Music (he was playing an accordion), he entered to study a play on Academy for Theater, Radio, Film, Television, where he graduated in 2005. For the diploma performance of Goldberg in "The Birthday party" by H. Pinter he was awarded with University Preseren award in 2005.

people.name: Jacqueline Govaert
people.aboutText: Jacqueline Govaert (born 20 April 1982) is a Dutch singer, songwriter, and pianist. She is best known as the leader of Dutch band Krezip. After Krezip disbanded in 2009, Govaert started a solo music career.

people.name: Sayaka Kamiya
people.aboutText:
Sayaka Kamiya (神谷涼, Kamiya Sayaka, born April 20, 1982) is a Japanese actress and model.
Kamiya is best known for her role as Satomi Noda in Battle Royale.

people.name: Dario Knežević
people.aboutText: Dario Knežević (born 20 April 1982) is a Croatian football defender who is currently a free agent.

people.name: Alar Varrak
people.aboutText: Alar Varrak (born 20 April 1982 in Jõgeva) is an Estonian basketball coach and a former point guard. He currently coaches the Estonian Championship team Kalev/Cramo. He is also the assistant coach of the Estonia national basketball team.

people.name: Danny Granger
people.aboutText: Danny Granger, Jr. (born April 20, 1983) is an American professional basketball player who last played for the Miami Heat of the National Basketball Association (NBA). He is mainly a small forward, though he also logs time at the power forward position.

people.name: Sebastian Ingrosso
people.aboutText: Sebastian Carmine Ingrosso (born 20 April 1983) is a Swedish DJ and electronic dance music producer. He was also a former member of the DJ supergroup Swedish House Mafia, together with friends Axwell and Steve Angello.

people.name: Miranda Kerr
people.aboutText: Miranda May Kerr (born 20 April 1983) is an Australian model. Kerr rose to prominence in 2007 as one of the Victoria's Secret Angels. She is the first Australian to participate in the Victoria's Secret campaign and also represented the Australian up-market department store chain David Jones.

people.name: Joanne King
people.aboutText: Joanne King (born April 20, 1983, Dublin, Ireland) is an Irish actress.

people.name: Patrice M'Bock
people.aboutText: Erik Segerstedt (born April 20, 1983 in Uddevalla) is a Swedish singer. As a student he attended the Adolf Fredrik's Music School in Stockholm. He was the runner-up to Markus Fagervall on the third season of Swedish version of Idol 2006.

people.name: Erik Segerstedt
people.aboutText: Joseph Patrice M'Bock (born 20 April 1983 in Edéa) is a former Cameroonian footballer.

people.name: Greg Smith
people.aboutText: Gregory Marc Smith (born 20 April 1983 in Johannesburg) is a South African cricketer. He is a right-handed batsman and a right-arm medium-fast bowler who plays for Essex. He had previously played for Derbyshire for eight years.

people.name: Fabio Staibano
people.aboutText:
Fabio Staibano (born Eboli, 20 April 1983) is an Italian rugby union footballer. He plays as a prop.
Staibano played at a youth level at Battipaglia Rugby, moving to Overmach Rugby Parma F.C., aged 18 years old, where he would stay from 2001/02 to 2007/08.

people.name: Yuri van Gelder
people.aboutText:
Nelson Évora GCIH (born 20 April 1984) is a Portuguese track and field athlete who specializes in the triple jump and long jump.
Évora is the current triple jump European indoor champion, and a former triple jump Olympic and world champion. Évora competes for Portugal and Portuguese club S.L. Benfica.

people.name: Nelson Évora
people.aboutText:
Yuri van Gelder (born 20 April 1983) is a Dutch gymnast, whose best discipline is the rings. His nickname is "Lord of the Rings".
Born in Waalwijk, Netherlands, Van Gelder took the gold in the men's rings at the 2005 European Championships held in Debrecen, Hungary.

people.name: Anthony Fasano
people.aboutText: Anthony Joseph Fasano (born April 20, 1984) is an American football tight end for the Tennessee Titans of the National Football League (NFL). He was drafted by the Dallas Cowboys of the National Football League (NFL) in the second round of the 2006 NFL Draft. He played college football at Notre Dame.

people.name: Tyson Griffin
people.aboutText: Tyson Lee Griffin (born April 20, 1984) is an American professional mixed martial artist currently competing in the Lightweight division.

people.name: Edixon Perea
people.aboutText:
Jenna Parker (born 20 April 1984 in Concord, Massachusetts) is a former professional US triathlete and a former member of the USA National Team.
In 2010 Shoemaker was number 49 in the World Championship Series ranking and number 5 in the USAT ranking.

people.name: Jenna Shoemaker
people.aboutText: Edixon Perea Valencia (born 20 April 1984 in Cali) is a Colombian footballer.

people.name: Harris Wittels
people.aboutText:
Amanda Fahy born in London on 20 April 1985 is a British actress most famous for her role as Shannon Parks in the BBC children's series Grange Hill.
Amanda joined the long running CBBC show in 2001 leaving the series in 2004.
She appeared in The Bill as Nikki McGrath in 2004 and a year later appeared in the Channel 4 made for TV drama Ahead of the Class about the notorious murder of head teacher Philip Lawrence.

people.name: Amanda Fahy
people.aboutText: Harris Lee Wittels (April 20, 1984 – February 19, 2015) was an American comedian, actor, writer, producer, and musician. He is best known for having been a writer for The Sarah Silverman Program, a writer and executive producer for Parks and Recreation, and a recurring guest on Comedy Bang!

people.name: Curt Hawkins
people.aboutText: Ehsan Jami (born April 20, 1985) is a Dutch politician. From March 7, 2006 until November 6, 2007 he was member of the city council of Leidschendam-Voorburg on behalf of the Dutch Labour Party (PvdA). From that date until 2010 he continued to be a member of the city council as independent member 'fraction Jami' .

people.name: Ehsan Jami
people.aboutText: Brian Joseph Myers (born April 20, 1985) is an American professional wrestler and promoter, better known by his ring name Curt Hawkins. He is best known for his time signed with WWE, and currently works for Global Force Wrestling (GFW).

people.name: Billy Magnussen
people.aboutText: Jadyn Douglas (previously known as Jadyn Maria), born April 20, 1985, is a Puerto Rican singer-songwriter and actress. At the age of seventeen, she was signed to EMI and later to Universal Motown in 2008, releasing a couple of singles to little commercial success. Douglas then started a country-pop trio with her sister (Jaclyn) and brother-in-law (Blake) in 2014 called Arten Way.

people.name: Jadyn Maria
people.aboutText: William Gregory "Billy" Magnussen (born April 20, 1985) is an American actor.

people.name: Brent Seabrook
people.aboutText: Cameron Troy Duncan (20 April 1986 – 12 November 2003) was a writer and director from New Zealand.

people.name: Cameron Duncan
people.aboutText: Brent Seabrook (born April 20, 1985) is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenseman and an alternate captain for the Chicago Blackhawks of the National Hockey League (NHL). He was selected in the first round, 14th overall, by the Blackhawks in the 2003 NHL Entry Draft out of the Western Hockey League (WHL). He played four seasons of junior with the Lethbridge Hurricanes before joining the Blackhawks in 2005–06, since then he has been a key component in their success including three Stanley Cup Championships.

people.name: John Patrick Amedori
people.aboutText:
John Patrick Amedori (born April 20, 1987) is an American actor and musician. He is perhaps best known for his portrayal of the thirteen-year-old Evan Treborn in The Butterfly Effect.
Amedori has also appeared in a number of television shows, including Law & Order, Nip/Tuck, Joan of Arcadia and Ghost Whisperer, as well as a part in the film Stick It.

people.aboutText: Alexander Anthony ″Alex″ Black (born April 20, 1989) is an American television and motion picture actor. Black was born in Redwood City, California. He has appeared in several popular movies; he mostly recently portrayed Seth Powers in Nickelodeon's hit series, Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide.

people.aboutText: Brandon Kyle Belt (born April 20, 1988) is an American professional baseball first baseman for the San Francisco Giants of Major League Baseball (MLB). He made his MLB debut during the 2011 season.. He was a member of the 2012 World Series and 2014 World Series championship teams with the Giants.

people.aboutText: Lu Han (born (1990-04-20)April 20, 1990), is a Chinese singer and actor who was a former member of the South Korean-Chinese boy band EXO, and its subgroup EXO-M. He is signed to S.M. Entertainment in South Korea and Avex Trax in Japan. In October 2014, Luhan filed a lawsuit to terminate his exclusive contract with SM Entertainment. In 2014, China National Radio ranked Lu Han the sixth among the top ten most popular entertainment stars in the country.

people.name: Marissa King
people.aboutText: Marissa Petra King (born April 20, 1991) is an English gymnast who represented Great Britain at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, China, as well as the 2007 and 2009 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships. Marissa is the daughter of a British father and Thai mother and began gymnastics at age 8. During her elite career she trained at the Huntingdon Olympic Gymnastics Club and currently competes for the University of Florida Gators NCAA gymnastics team.

people.name: Ondřej Kraják
people.aboutText: Ondřej Kraják (born 20 April 1991) is a Czech footballer who currently plays for FC Hradec Králové. His playing position is forward.

people.name: Luke Kuechly
people.aboutText: Luke August Kuechly (/ˈkikli/; born April 20, 1991) is an American football Linebacker for the Carolina Panthers of the National Football League (NFL). He was drafted by the Panthers ninth overall in the 2012 NFL Draft. He played college football at Boston College, and was recognized twice as a consensus All-American.

people.name: Allie Will
people.aboutText:
Allie Will (born April 20, 1991) is an American tennis player.
Will has won eleven doubles titles on the ITF tour in her career. On July 22, 2013, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 293.

people.name: Marko Meerits

Anastasia Vdovenco (born 20 April 1994 in Chișinău) is a Moldovan tennis player.
Vdovenco has won one singles and three doubles titles on the ITF tour in her career. On 13 October 2014, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 565.

people.name: Carly Rose Sonenclar
people.aboutText: Carly Rose Sonenclar (born April 20, 1999) is an American singer and teen actress. In December 2012, she became the runner-up on the second season of the American version of the The X Factor.

people.name: Twist Magic
people.aboutText: Twist Magic (20 April 2002 – 15 December 2010) was a French-bred, British-trained National Hunt horse trained by Paul Nicholls. He specialised as a two mile chaser, and recorded many top class wins such as the Tingle Creek in 2007 and 2009 and the Victor Chandler Chase in 2010. He suffered a fatal injury while racing in the rearranged Peterborough Chase at Newbury and had to be put down.

people.name: Zarkandar
people.aboutText: Zarkandar (foaled 20 April 2007) is an Irish-bred, British-trained Thoroughbred racehorse who competes in National Hunt races. A half-brother to the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe winner Zarkava he won one of his three flat races before being gelded and becoming a specialist hurdler. He was the best juvenile hurdler of the 2010/2011 National Hunt season when he won the Adonis Juvenile Novices' Hurdle, Triumph Hurdle and Anniversary 4-Y-O Novices' Hurdle.
